article.headline: Cleveland St. 83, Milwaukee 57
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Trevon Harmon scored 15 points to lead six Cleveland State players in double figures and the Vikings cruised to an 83-57 win over Milwaukee on Sunday to remain tied for first place in the Horizon League. Cleveland State (17-4, 7-2), which has won two straight and five of its last six, is tied with Valparaiso atop the league. The Vikings shot 69.2 percent in the second half (18 of 26) while the Panthers shot only 26.9 percent (7 of 26). Cleveland State also dominated the first half, leading by as many as 13 and 36-28 at the break. Up 38-30 with 18:11 remaining, the Vikings put the game away with a 13-0 run, holding Milwaukee scoreless for 3 1/2 minutes. Tim Kamczyc, Jeremy Montgomery and Anton Grady added 12 points apiece for Cleveland State. Aaron Pogue scored 11 and D'Aundray Brown 10. James Haarsma's 15 points led the Panthers (13-8, 6-3).
